  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Architectural Coordinator",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Manage the transmission of documents and drawings to clients and subcontractors, ensuring that updated drawings are issued.</li>\n  <li>Prepare method of statement and work procedures.</li>\n  <li>Ensure work is executed according to the method statements.</li>\n  <li>Conduct weekly or monthly meetings with subcontractors to update project progress.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate construction activities to comply with QOSHE (Quality, Occupational Safety, Health, and Environment) requirements.</li>\n  <li>Conduct project risk impact assessments.</li>\n  <li>Review construction drawings for accuracy.</li>\n  <li>Manage the procurement of resources, and monitor and control material usage on-site to prevent unnecessary wastage or incorrect use.</li>\n  <li>Assist the Project Manager in coordinating with consultants on change orders.</li>\n  <li>Organize labor, equipment, and materials for daily site activities.</li>\n  <li>Perform material receiving inspections and maintain material records, ensuring all delivery orders are returned to HQ for documentation.</li>\n  <li>Prepare daily reports, and perform and maintain inspection records.</li>\n  <li>Any other duties assigned</li>\n</ul>",
